---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="About">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">About SiteAge.org</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none space-y-4">
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg">
        SiteAge.org is a website age certification platform. We trace the origins of websites
        using the Internet Archive's Wayback Machine and generate verifiable age badges.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">How It Works</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600">
        <li>Enter a domain name to look up</li>
        <li>We query the Wayback Machine CDX API for the earliest archived snapshot</li>
        <li>The earliest successful snapshot date becomes the "birth date"</li>
        <li>You get a certificate page and an embeddable SVG badge</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Verification</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600">
        Website owners can claim their domain through DNS TXT record or meta tag verification.
        Verified domains receive a gold "Established" badge and can submit evidence for an
        earlier birth date if the Wayback Machine didn't capture the earliest version.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Open Source</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600">
        SiteAge.org is open source under the MIT license.
        <a href="https://github.com/user/siteage.org" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          View on GitHub
        </a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
